What do you want to be when you grow up?

When someone asks that we try to answer it with a consise response. We try to answer it with a single answer. Wouldn't it be sad if that were true?

Many people get asked this question during their educational years. Imagine how difficult this is. You've been on the earth for under a decade and you're asked to make a statement that will impact your entire lifespan of nearly 100 years. Ouch, that's hard. We have an aphorism in project management that goes,<em>you make all your decisions at the beginning of the project when you know the least about it.</em> It's hard enough to do this in project management, but when the project is your life it can be pretty devastating.

